     <font class="TallRed">Dream I had last night...<a name="108835573834624197">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          Had this funny dream last night. I'm afraid to talk about it because some people might get the wrong idea but I'll leave comments open.<br /><br />I'm driving on my way to some place when I suddenly take a right down a road that looks very familiar. I stop my car and knock on a door that looks very familiar. The door opens and it's the mother of a girl I dated a while back. <blockquote>Mom: Oh, hello Joe. What a surprise it is to see you here.<br />Me: yeah, I feel the same way. I'm not entirely sure why I'm here too.<br />Mom: are you looking for [GIRL NAME]?<br />Me: Yes, I guess I <em>am</em> looking for her.<br />Mom: Well, lemme go get her.<br />Me: Thanks.</blockquote>She leads me in the door and lets me sit on a chair while I wait. I start getting worried because I can't remember why I'm in this place and why I'm about to speak to one of my ex's. That's when I look down to see that there is an envelope in my hand with her name written on it in my handwriting. Suddenly, I realize why I came here and everything makes sense-- allowing my anxiety fade quickly. [GIRL NAME] walks into the room with her head tilted slightly, questioning with body language why I have come to her house after almost three years. I rise to my feet, smiling.<blockquote>Ex: Hi Joe...<br />Me: Hi, umm, did I come at a bad time?<br />Ex: No, I just never would have expected to see you in my house again.<br />Me: Well, I feel that I have a very good reason to be here. I've been thinking about this for a while and I decided that it couldn't sit in my mind any longer. So here.</blockquote>I take a step closer to her, who now looks totally confused and nervous. I put out my hand and give her the envelope with her name on it.<blockquote>Ex: what is this?<br />Me: Read it when I leave.</blockquote>Still in the dream I see myself from a third person point of view walk out of the door and close it behind me. I get into my car, back out of her driveway, and ride off into the distance. Then I see her right where I left her, in her living room. She takes the letter into her father's office, rips it into quarters and tosses it into the garbage. She begins IMing her friends with the computer that sits right in front of it, telling them what happened. One of her friends ask: "What was in the letter??"<br /><br />She looks down at the trash bin where the torn letter rests on top. She notices that the pages are exposed out of the envelope a bit, but there is no visible handwriting anywhere. She bends over and picks out three piece of the four and unfolds the letter inside. Nothing.<br /><br />Confused, she takes the last piece out of the trash can and unfolds it. In the top, left-hand corner of the letter there are four words, followed by a period. She reads it once, puts it down on the desk, laughs to herself, picks it up again to recheck, throws it in the garbage, then pulls her keyboard towards her to respond to her inquiring friend. She types to her friend, "All it said was: <strong>'Vote democratic this election.'</strong> with a smiley face at the end."<br />
